\par }{\b\f1\fs20\insrsid8482110 Features}{\f1\fs20\insrsid8482110 :
\par 
\par A 'Needy List' button, under which all the needy units will be listed.  This button can be dragged around the screen and determines where your list will show up.
\par 
\par Each needy unit is displayed in a targeting box, each of which features:
\par - A frame that displays the buffs and debuffs on that unit.
\par \tab - Each buff and debuff has a tooltip associated with it, so you aren't required to know what the icons all mean.
\par - Name, health, and mana (or whatever other power type that player uses).
\par \tab - Mouse-over the health and mana to display the numeric values of them.
\par - A colour coded background.
\par \tab - The color of the frame is based on the color you choose in your configuration.
\par - A frame that displays icons representing the current needs of that unit.
\par \tab - Simply click on a need icon and that need will be cured.
\par \tab - For the heal need, you can set up spells or items to use in the 'configure spells' dialog box.  To use an item, simply place its name within square brackets.
\par 
